that couples to the dynamical equation for the width parameter $B$, and both in turn determine the dynamics of the norm $N$. Since the approximation relies on the Gaussian to be well localized, the imaginary part of $B$ encodes the reliability of the approximation. In what follows we shall consider an example of a model for a $PT$-symmetric waveguide to demonstrate the quality of the approximation for initial Gaussian states, as well as the influence of the beam shape on the propagation. 

